{"title_page": "Jeff Stryker", "text_new": "{{Infobox adult biography\n| name            = Jeff Stryker\n| image           = Jeffrobe1.jpg\n| caption         = Jeff Stryker in 2007\n| birth_name      = Charles Casper Peyton<ref name=rn>{{cite web|last=Javors|first=Steve|url=http://www.xbiz.com/news/18743 |title=Gay Porn Icon Wants Folk Club Shut Down|publisher=XBIZ|date=2006-12-21|accessdate=2010-02-27}}</ref>\n| birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|1962|08|21}}\n| birth_place     = [[Carmi, Illinois]], USA\n| death_date      = \n| death_place     = \n| spouse          = \n| height          = {{height|ft=5|in=9}}\n| weight          = \n| alias           = \n| number_of_films = \n| website         = \n}}\n'''Jeff Stryker''' (born '''Charles Casper Peyton''',<ref name=rn/> August 21, 1962) is an American [[pornographic actor|porn star]] who has starred in bisexual, gay, and straight [[adult films]]. He lives in California.\n\n==Early life==\nJeff Stryker grew up in Springfield, Illinois. His father was a car salesman and his mother was a nurse.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.therialtoreport.com/2013/12/01/jeff-stryker-porns-enigmatic-star-podcast-26/|title=Jeff Stryker: Porn's Enigmatic Star Podcast 26|work=The Rialto Report|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref> At age 13, he was sent to military school by his parents, who got a divorce while he was away. {{citation needed|date=March 2016}}\n\n==Pre-film career==\nJeff Stryker worked as a stripper and delivered balloon-o-grams before a local photographer sent shots of him to gay adult film director John Travis in California.<ref name=Jeff>[http://www.therialtoreport.com/2013/12/01/jeff-stryker-porns-enigmatic-star-podcast-26/ \"Jeff Stryker: Porn's Enigmatic Star\"], [http://www.therialtoreport.com/ The Rialto Report], December 1, 2013</ref>\n\n==Film career and sexuality==\nStryker is primarily known as a performer in gay pornography films, although ''Jamie Loves Jeff'' was one of the biggest selling heterosexual adult movies of all time for its producer, [[Vivid Entertainment]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://avn.com/business/articles/video/vivid-releases-dvd-version-of-straight-jeff-stryker-videos-36710.html|title=AVN - Vivid Releases DVD Version Of Straight Jeff Stryker Videos|last=|first=|date=2003-09-23|website=AVN.com|publisher=avn.com|accessdate=2020-03-13}}</ref> He describes himself (in a somewhat joking fashion) as sexually \"universal\".<ref name=Simpson1994 >{{citation|last=Simpson|first=Mark|year=1994|title=Male impersonators: men performing masculinity|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-0-415-90991-4 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XGL8pqKjdw0C |page=131}}</ref> He has also said, \"I don\u2019t define myself as anything.\"<ref>[http://wehonews.com/z/wehonews/archive/page.php?articleID=737] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061127135854/http://wehonews.com/z/wehonews/archive/page.php?articleID=737 |date=November 27, 2006 }}</ref>\n\nHe also tried acting, starring in a 1989 Italian-produced horror film called ''[[After Death]]'' (Revenge of the Zombies), in which he was credited as Chuck Peyton. Later in the American DVD release, the name Jeff Stryker was used as well. A trailer interview was added with Stryker's describing the experience he had while shooting this movie in Manila. Stryker also starred in the short film  by German cult director [[Rosa von Praunheim]] ''Can I Be Your Bratwurst, Please?''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/12739.html|archive-url=https://archive.today/20120709133835/http://business.avn.com/articles/12739.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2012-07-09|title=Outfest Spotlights Gay Porn|publisher=Business.avn.com|date=1999-10-01|accessdate=2010-02-27}}</ref>  Stryker also appeared in a 1995 German television movie ''Der schwarze Fluch'' (Black Curse) starring James Brolin,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0111090/ |title=Der schwarze Fluch - T\u00f6dliche Leidenschaften (TV Movie 1995)|work=IMDb|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref> as well as the 1988 Italian feature ''Dirty Love''.\n\n==Awards and tributes==\n* [[AVN Hall of Fame]] inductee<ref name=hall>{{cite web|url=http://www.avnawards.com/halloffame.php |title=25th Annual AVN Awards Show |accessdate=9 September 2014 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090415212412/http://www.avnawards.com/halloffame.php |archivedate=15 April 2009 }}</ref>\n* [[GayVN Awards|GayVN]] Hall of Fame inductee<ref name=\"gayvn\">{{cite web|title=GayVN Hall of Fame listing |url=http://gayvnawards.avn.com/noms/hall-of-fame.html |accessdate=5 November 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111105121614/http://gayvnawards.avn.com/noms/hall-of-fame.html |archivedate= 5 November 2011 }}</ref>\n* 2000 [[Grabby Awards|Grabby]] Wall of Fame inductee<ref name=\"grabby\">{{cite web|title=2000 Grabby Award winners |url=http://www.grabbys.com/a1.grab.00.win.html |accessdate=5 November 2016 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20020609110405/http://www.grabbys.com/a1.grab.00.win.html |archivedate= 9 June 2002 }}</ref>\n* 2004 [[Hustler]] Porn Walk of Fame<ref name=\"hustler\">{{cite web|title=Sharon Mitchell and Jeff Stryker Inducted into Hustler Hollywood Porn Walk of Fame|url=https://avn.com/business/articles/video/Sharon-Mitchell-and-Jeff-Stryker-Inducted-into-Hustler-Hollywood-Porn-Walk-of-Fame-37555.html|accessdate=5 November 2016}}</ref>\n* 1986 [[XRCO Award|XRCO]] Best Actor (Gay)<ref name=\"xrco\">{{cite web|title=XRCO Gay Award winners|url=http://www.dirtybob.com/xrco/hall.htm|accessdate=5 November 2016}}</ref> \n* Stryker was featured in a 1991 portrait by artists [[Pierre et Gilles]].<ref name=\"salon\">{{cite web|last1=Helfand|first1=Glen|title=Pierre et Gilles|url=http://www.salon.com/2001/03/01/pierre_gilles/|website=salon.com|accessdate=5 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Merchandising==\nThe Jeff Stryker Cock and Balls, a [[dildo]] fashioned from a cast of his penis, is widely sold in sex stores. The dildo was academically analyzed in a paper presented at the 1995 [[Bowling Green State University]] Conference in Cultural Studies: ''Lesbian Pornography and Transformation: Foucault, Bourdieu, and de Certeau Make Sense of the Jeff Stryker Dildo'', by Mary T. Conway, then a graduate student at Temple University.{{Citation needed|reason=Couldn't find any papers going by this title|date=December 2019}} The sex toy is notable not only for being popular, but also as Stryker and the manufacturer of the item litigated for the rights to its likeness as part of Stryker's [[intellectual property]]. The case eventually reached a mutually acceptable resolution (see {{slink||Legal Battles}}).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salon.com/health/sex/urge/world/1999/03/18/feature/index.html|title=Original sin|author=Janis Cooke Newman|work=salon.com|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref> In a 1999 ''[[Salon (website)|Salon]]'' article written by Jeff Stryker, a New York journalist and the porn actor's namesake, the dildo is even described as an object of higher culture.<ref name=Salon>{{cite journal |author=Stryker, Jeff <sub>(''namesake of the porn actor'')</sub> |date=18 March 1999 |title=Will The Real Jeff Stryker Please Rise |journal=[[Salon.com]] |url=http://www.salon.com/urge/feature/1999/03/18feature.html |accessdate=2007-12-17}}</ref> It was mentioned in [[Allan Gurganus]]' 1997 novel ''Plays Well with Others'', where the novel's narrator cleans up a closet filled with dildos, the premium find being \"a Jeff Stryker, a monster, but somehow Roman in its genial fluted civic beauty.\"<ref>{{cite book |last=Gurganus |first=Allan |authorlink=Allan Gurganus |title=Plays Well with Others |origyear=1997 |date=2 February 1999 |publisher=Vintage |isbn=978-0-375-70203-7|page=9 |chapter=Prologue : The Comedy of Friends}}</ref>\n\nStryker has released a compact disc (''Wild Buck'') of country music that he performed, and in his pornographic video ''Bigger Than Life'', he performed a rock song of the same name.{{Citation needed|date=February 2007}}\n\n==Reaction from other celebrities==\n* Filmmaker and author [[John Waters (filmmaker)|John Waters]] called Jeff Stryker \u201cthe [[Cary Grant]] of porno.\u201d<ref name=dreamlandnews>{{cite web|url=http://www.dreamlandnews.com/print/articles/raygun.shtml|title=Beyond the Valley of the Pulsating Colostomy Bags: An interview with John Waters!|work=dreamlandnews.com|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref>\n* American comedian [[Margaret Cho]]'s routines involve her love for his films. In her show, ''Assassin'', she discusses in detail the many places one can use the dildo. Stryker had given Cho his commercially produced action figure.<ref name=margaretcho>{{Cite web |url=http://www.margaretcho.com/blog/2004/03/10/jeff-stryker.html |title=Margaret Cho's blog: Jeff Stryker |access-date=2008-08-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081225212426/http://www.margaretcho.com/blog/2004/03/10/jeff-stryker.html |archive-date=2008-12-25 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* In her autobiography, [[Traci Lords]] describes him as \u201chandsome but rather dumb looking\u201d after he gave her scornful looks backstage during a [[Century City Civic Center]] [[Thierry Mugler]] Fashion show.\n\n==Legal battles==\nStryker later sued Health Devices Inc. and California Publishers Liquidating Corp. for over $1&nbsp;million for breach of contract and piracy when they sold a bootleg dildo of his genitals without paying him sufficiently. The case was heard before a judge in Los Angeles, who eventually brokered a deal whereby the case was dismissed upon payment of $25,000 to Stryker and the return and right to reproduce all items which Stryker endorsed.<ref name=Salon/>\n\nStryker has had arguments with Kulak's Woodshed, a folk-music nightclub, that is next door to his office. He claims that the club causes disturbance normally associated with large late-night urban venues: noise, drugs, unruly patrons, vandalism, graffiti, public urination and parking headaches. James Britton, who operates a floor covering business on the other side of the club, also complains that the club has damaged his business. In January 2009, the ''L.A. Weekly'' reported that Stryker blamed the nightclub for preventing him from completing his autobiography, as the noise and crowds disturbed his concentration. \u201c(My writing has) been put on perpetual hold until I can get myself back together,\u201d he told the newspaper. \u201cI got a $25,000 advance on (the book) but could never complete it.\u201d\n\nBut Paul Kulak counter claims (according to the ''L.A. Weekly'') that Stryker has made threats to him and the club's customers: \u201cHe constantly reminds me he\u2019s a firearms expert and will hide behind his back door when I dump the trash. Once, he started making mechanical gun clicks. I could see he had a pistol in his hand as he was dry-firing it... I\u2019m willing to risk my life to keep this [club] going.\u201d Stryker responded to Kulak's claim and was quoted as saying, \"That guy is so out there!\"<ref>Mikulan, Steven. [http://www.laweekly.com/2009-01-08/news/the-porn-star-39-s-revenge-formerly-known-as-jeff-stryker-charles-peyton-has-turned-his-toxic-feud-over-the-folk-music-club-kulak-39-s-woodshed-into-a-real-life-and-online-obsession/ \"The Porn Star's Revenge: Formerly Known as Jeff Stryker, Charles Peyton Has Turned His Toxic Feud Over the Folk-Music Club Kulak's Woodshed Into a Real-Life Online Obsession,\"] ''L.A. Weekly''. Retrieved 2009-1-12.</ref>\n\n==Stage shows==\nStryker appeared in ''A Sophisticated Evening with Jeff Stryker'' in Los Angeles, Summer 2006 and in Provincetown, Massachusetts, Summer 2007.<ref name=autogenerated2>Michael Persson, \"From the Editor\", ''Provincetown Magazine'' Vol. 30, issue 19, August 16, 2007.</ref> The show was produced by comedy writer [[Bruce Vilanch]]. In the show, Stryker performed a comic monologue about his life and adventures in adult films, conducted a \"porn acting demo\" comedy skit with an audience member, and danced in a nude finale where he greeted the audience.\n\nFrom 1999 through 2001, Stryker performed in a stage show called ''Hard Time'', a comedy send-up of gay porn prison films. In the finale, Stryker danced nude. After the play, Stryker met with the audience at the door. The show toured several cities including New York,<ref>{{cite web | last=Sands | first=Brian | title= Jeff Stryker does Hard Time | website=Ambush Magazine, Volume 17/Issue 15 - Adventures | url=http://www.ambushmag.com/is1599/tadvent.htm | access-date=2019-03-11}}</ref> San Francisco,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sfgate.com/performance/article/Porn-God-Takes-To-the-Stage-Jeff-Stryker-s-2948258.php |title=Porn God Takes to the Stage / Jeff Stryker's ''Hard Time'' in S.F.|work=SFGate|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref> Chicago,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagoreader.com/chicago/jeff-stryker-does-hard-time/Content?oid=905230 |title=Jeff Stryker Does Hard Time|work=Chicago Reader|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref> and Houston.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.houstonpress.com/2000-10-26/calendar/fun-with-dick/full/ |title=Fun with Dick|author=Lee Williams|date=23 October 2006|work=houstonpress.com|accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Selected filmography==\n\n===Gay and solo===\n* ''Jeff Stryker Does Hard Time'' 2001\n* ''Stryker'' 2000 solo/masturbation\n* ''Jeff Stryker\u2019s Underground'' 1997\n* ''Santa\u2019s Cummin\u2019!'' 1996 solo/masturbation\n* ''J.S. Big Time'' 1995\n* ''The Tease'' 1994 solo/masturbation\n* ''How to Enlarge Your Penis'' 1993 solo/masturbation\n* ''10 Plus'' 1992 solo/masturbation\n* ''10 Plus Volume 2'' 1992 solo/masturbation\n* ''Busted'' 1991\n* ''In Hot Pursuit'' 1991\n* ''Powertool 2: Breaking Out''\n* ''Just You & Me'' 1990 solo/masturbation\n* ''On the Rocks'' 1990\n* ''Stryker\u2019s Best: Powerful Sex'' 1989\n* ''The Look'' 1987\n* ''Stryker Force'' 1987\n* ''In Hot Pursuit'' 